6: One fresh pot, coming right up!
11:
Thank you, Alk. The tea you brew
always tastes a little better.
14:
I also baked some cookies. They came
out pretty good if I do say so myself.
18:
I can see that—and quite a variety of
flavors to analyze as well.
21:
Analyze? I mean, they're mostly flour.
You know, on carefree days like this—
33:
Wh-What's all of this out of nowhere?!
More importantly, I was just about to—
37:
The Guild's put out a request!
Come on, I bet it'll be fun if we all do
it together!
42:
H-hold on! I never said I'd go with—
Hey! My... My tea and cookies...
46:
I thought we'd be exploring a dungeon
for treasure or involve something
more... heroic.
50:
There's nothing unheroic about
clean-up duty! Not to mention the
pay isn't half bad.
53:
We appreciate all you do for us, Yuna.
I don't know what we'd do without
you!
56:
No worries, ma'am! Whenever you
need our services again,
just put out the word!
59:
Yuna, I've finished cleaning my area.
There isn't a single speck of dust
within this three-centimeter radius.
63:
Well, now there's just one pristine
spot...
66:
That'll do just fine, Stella! Now that
we're done here, onto our next quest!
71: Wait... You mean we're not done yet?
82: So THIS is what you meant.
85:
The sheep must all be shepherded
into the barn by sunset.
That's the quest.
88:
They don't look like they wanna
move at all...
92:
Oh yeah? If it's a mover you want,
it's a mover you'll get!
99:
Hmm... Yes, I see. Lovesick, you say?
That's rough, buddy.
102:
Wait, you can't actually understand
them, can you?
105:
But you have to understand. Love...
Love is a battlefield! So FIGHT with
ALL of your heart!
111:
I can't believe you got them to move
with such a hackneyed—wait, more
importantly, you can talk to animals?!
115:
Huh? I mean, yeah. My dad taught me
Sheeplish when I was a little girl.
120:
I've never heard of such a language...
Could you tell me more?
125:
Ahaha! I'm just pullin' your legs.
I dunno, I guess I just kinda feel it out,
you know? We raised a lot of sheep
back where I'm from.
130: You can just... feel out... lovesickness?
134:
Anywho, it looks like we're almost
done, so hang in there!
145:
Good work, everyone! Here's our pay
for the day.
150:
Whoa... I wasn't expecting to earn THIS
much. Do you usually take on these
types of jobs?
155:
Yup! Wait, that doesn't make me seem
boring or something, does it?
159:
The boring stuff's just as important
too, you know! Like being in charge of
food and, uh... being in charge of food!
163:
Y-yeah, you're right! Back home, my
teacher used to say that helping
those close to you comes first!
171:
Yeah! Just someone I looked up to,
you know? I wanted to become
an adventurer just like him!
175: He sounds like a good person.
178:
You bet! He'd drop whatever he was
doing to help a person need! What
a badass, right?
181:
He had a great big belly laugh, and
would always tell me not to sweat
the small stuff.
185: So that's where that comes from.
189:
Anywho, thanks for today! And sorry
if it was a little... boring compared to
your usual action-packed stuff.
193: I had a great time, Yuna.
196: Not only that, look at all this cash!
200:
Heh...
I knew I could count on you guys!
204:
Perhaps next time you could teach
me how to speak Sheeplish as well.
208:
Sure thing! I'll be counting on the
both of ya!
